---
description: Laravel backend architecture and code quality rules
globs:
  - "app/**/*.php"
  - "routes/**/*.php"
  - "database/**/*.php"
  - "tests/**/*.php"
alwaysApply: false
---

Follow Laravel conventions already present in the repository.

- Keep controllers thin.
- Use Form Requests for non-trivial validation.
- Use Policies for model ownership and authorization.
- Use a dedicated ProductQuery for search, filters, sorting, and pagination.
- Use an Action or Service for checkout and order cancellation.
- Use database transactions and row locks for inventory-changing workflows.
- Use Eloquent relationships and eager loading.
- Do not add a repository layer without an explicit requirement.
- Do not use `$request->all()` for writes.
- Do not trust client price, totals, stock, role, or order status.
- Do not concatenate user input into SQL.
- Add feature tests for success, validation failure, and authorization failure.

- Store prices and totals as integer Vietnamese đồng values.
- Do not use floating point for money.
- Support optional color and storage on variants for charging accessories.
- Recalculate cart and checkout totals on the server.
